{
  "texts": [
    "The retrieval module searches the external data sources for relevant information, retrieves the pertinent data, and sends it back to the reverse proxy layer.",
    "The reverse proxy layer then combines the original query with the retrieved data, forming an enriched query that is forwarded to the Llama model.",
    "The Llama model processes the enriched query, generating a response that incorporates the retrieved information, resulting in a factually accurate and contextually appropriate output.",
    "The algorithm 1 describes the detailed process:The data flow within the system can be visualized as follows:Algorithm 1 Reverse Proxy Style RAG Integration Require: Query Q 1: Q ← Intercept(Q) ▷ Reverse Proxy Layer 2: R ← Retrieve(Q) ▷ Retrieval Module 3: E ← Enrich(Q, R) ▷ CombineOriginal Query with Retrieved Data 4: Response ← Generate(E) ▷ Llama Model 5: return Response Q → Reverse Proxy Layer → Retrieval Module → Reverse Proxy Layer (enrichment) → Llama Model → Response Data Sources and Retrieval MechanismThe retrieval mechanism is a critical component of the reverse proxy-style RAG system, responsible for accessing and extracting relevant information from external data sources.",
    "The choice of data sources plays a vital role in determining the effectiveness of the retrieval process."
  ]
}